  "text": "The C++ source files implementing HTTP connection manager route matching in Envoy v1.31.2 are organized across several key directories:\n\n**HTTP Connection Manager Core (source/common/http/)**\nThe HTTP connection manager implementation is in conn_manager_impl.cc/h, which handles incoming HTTP connections and manages request/response processing. It coordinates with filter_manager.cc/h for HTTP filter chain execution. Configuration is handled by conn_manager_config.h, with utility functions in conn_manager_utility.cc/h. Route-related utilities are in null_route_impl.cc/h and route_config_update_requster.cc/h.\n\n**HTTP Connection Manager Filter Extension (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/)**\nThe extension integration layer provides config.cc/h for configuring the HTTP connection manager as a network filter.\n\n**Router Configuration and Matching (source/common/router/)**\nThe core routing logic is implemented through several key files:\n\n- **config_impl.cc/h**: Contains the Matchable interface and implementations for VirtualHostImpl and multiple route entry types (PrefixRouteEntryImpl, PathRouteEntryImpl, RegexRouteEntryImpl, UriTemplateMatcherRouteEntryImpl, ConnectRouteEntryImpl, PathSeparatedPrefixRouteEntryImpl). Also contains RouteMatcher, RouteMatchAction, and CommonVirtualHostImpl classes that handle virtual host selection and route matching logic.\n\n- **router.cc/h**: The main router filter implementation that dispatches matched routes to upstream clusters, including filter utility functions and request handling.\n\n- **config_utility.cc/h**: Utility functions for route configuration parsing and manipulation.\n\n- **context_impl.cc/h**: Router context implementation for request-specific routing state.\n\n- **vhds.cc/h**: Virtual Host Discovery Service implementation for dynamic virtual host configuration.\n\n- **rds_impl.cc/h**: Route Discovery Service implementation for dynamic route configuration.\n\n- **scoped_config_impl.cc/h and scoped_rds.cc/h**: Scoped routing configuration implementation for per-scope routing rules.\n\n- **header_parser.cc/h and reset_header_parser.cc/h**: Header matching and manipulation during routing.\n\n- **metadatamatchcriteria_impl.cc/h and tls_context_match_criteria_impl.cc/h**: Metadata and TLS-based route matching criteria.\n\n- **upstream_request.cc/h and upstream_codec_filter.cc/h**: Upstream request handling after route selection.\n\n- **retry_state_impl.cc/h and router_ratelimit.cc/h**: Retry and rate limiting policy implementation for routes.\n\n- **delegating_route_impl.cc/h**: Route delegation and wrapping implementation.\n\n- **debug_config.cc/h**: Debug configuration for routing decisions.\n\n- **route_config_update_receiver_impl.cc/h and route_provider_manager.cc/h**: Route configuration update handling.\n\n- **static_route_provider_impl.cc/h**: Static route provider for non-dynamic routes.\n\n- **shadow_writer_impl.cc/h**: Shadow traffic routing implementation.\n\n- **string_accessor_impl.h**: String accessor utilities for route matching.\n\n- **header_parser_utils.cc**: Utility functions for header parsing in routing context.\n\n**Matcher Infrastructure (source/common/matcher/)**\nGeneric matching infrastructure is implemented in matcher.cc/h with specialized matchers: exact_map_matcher.h, prefix_map_matcher.h, map_matcher.h, list_matcher.h, field_matcher.h, value_input_matcher.h, and validation_visitor.h.\n\n**HTTP Matching (source/common/http/matching/)**\nHTTP-specific matching inputs are in inputs.cc/h, with data implementation in data_impl.h and status code matching in status_code_input.cc/h.\n\n**HTTP Router Filter Extension (source/extensions/filters/http/router/)**\nThe HTTP router filter configuration is in config.cc/h.\n\nThese files collectively implement the complete flow of: receiving HTTP requests in the connection manager -> determining the appropriate virtual host -> matching the request to a route -> dispatching to the selected upstream cluster."
